              Malik until 2015. The group was formed after the five members
              auditioned for the seventh season of the British singing
              competition The X Factor separately in 2010. Although they
              didn't win the show, judges Simon Cowell, Nicole Scherzinger,
              and Louis Walsh thought they were too talented to send home and
              put them together as a group. The group finished in third place
              and signed with Cowell's record label, Syco Records.
